### Test Approval Status Endpoint
### You can use this file with REST Client extension in VS Code

### 1. Approve a record (replace :id with actual record ID)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/admin/records/1/approval
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: adminToken=your_admin_token_here

{
  "approvalStatus": "approved"
}

###

### 2. Disapprove a record
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/admin/records/1/approval
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: adminToken=your_admin_token_here

{
  "approvalStatus": "disapproved"
}

###

### 3. Test with invalid status (should return 400 error)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/admin/records/1/approval
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: adminToken=your_admin_token_here

{
  "approvalStatus": "pending"
}

###

### 4. Test with non-existent record (should return 404 error)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/admin/records/99999/approval
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: adminToken=your_admin_token_here

{
  "approvalStatus": "approved"
}

###

### 5. Get all records (should include approvalStatus field)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/admin/records?page=1&pageSize=10
Cookie: adminToken=your_admin_token_here

###

### 6. Get single record (should include approvalStatus field)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/admin/records/1
Cookie: adminToken=your_admin_token_here
